

## Metadata


Headers:

`#alias actor shortname longname`
`#require act actid`

The following external functions are implicitly applied to each story:
```
EXTERNAL run_command(commandText)   // runs a minecraft command with the reader as the source
EXTERNAL read_global(keyString)     // stores a value to the series global register
EXTERNAL write_global(keyString)    // reads a value from the series global register, or zero if not present.
```

## Formatting
- All Placeholder tags
- <PLAYER_NAME>

## Lines
Default expression is "neutral" if not provided. Actor is placed
in the first available slot, from the middle outward. There are
6 slots numbered 0-5.

`name expression slot: texthere`

You can add tags to lines like
`#hide actorid`
`#sound soundid volume pitch`

## Hints

Testing if a player has an item:
```~ temp hasItem = run_command("/clear @s minecraft:cookie[minecraft:custom_name='Rare Cookie'] 0")```
The above will only test without clearing. Changing the value will let you remove items.
For more complicated tests, you could try something like
```~ temp hasItemInSlot = run_command("/execute if items entity @s hotbar.* minecraft:cookie[minecraft:custom_name="hama_onion"]")```

Here's an example scenario:
```
    lulu: come back with a cookie please!
-   (no_cookie)
    ~temp hasCookie = run_command("clear @s cookie 0")
    {no_cookie > 1: lulu: Did you find any? ;)}

+   [I'll be back later.]
    You have {hasCookie} cookies. {hasCookie > 0: Why are you not sharing?}
    -> no_cookie

*   {hasCookie> 0} Here you go!
    ~ run_command("clear @s cookie 1")
    lulu thank you so much! #sound minecraft:entity.arrow.hit_player
    goodbye! #hide lulu
    -> END
```
